description: Jams stretched more than 430 miles (700km) in total just hours before new measures came into force.
title: Covid-19: Record traffic around Paris as second French lockdown begins
title_page: Covid-19: Record traffic around Paris as second French lockdown begins - BBC News
maintext: "We're asking people to stay at home and Parisians to stay in Paris. You can well understand that if 4,000 people from Paris invade and one-third of them are infected without knowing, obviously it risks spreading rapidly," wrote one commentator in the local Sud Ouest (South-West) newspaper.
